# UltraFast HTTP Client ğŸš€

A **production-ready**, high-performance HTTP client for Python built with Rust and Tokio. Featuring complete sync/async support, HTTP/2, WebSocket, Server-Sent Events, and enterprise-grade features.

## âœ¨ **Key Features**

- **ğŸš€ Blazing Fast** - 2-7x faster than popular Python HTTP libraries
- **ğŸ”„ Sync & Async** - Complete synchronous and asynchronous API support  
- **ğŸŒ Protocol Support** - HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2 with intelligent fallback
- **ğŸ”Œ Real-time** - WebSocket and Server-Sent Events (SSE) support
- **ğŸ›¡ï¸ Enterprise Ready** - Authentication, retries, rate limiting, middleware
- **âš¡ High Performance** - Connection pooling, compression, and memory efficiency
- **ğŸ¯ Production Ready** - Comprehensive error handling and observability

## ğŸ¯ **Why Choose UltraFast?**

| Feature | UltraFast | requests | httpx | aiohttp |
|---------|-----------|----------|-------|---------|
| **Speed** | ğŸš€ **2-7x faster** | Standard | Fast | Fast |
| **Async Support** | âœ… Native | âŒ | âœ… | âœ… |
| **HTTP/2** | âœ… Auto | âŒ | âœ… | âŒ |
| **WebSocket** | âœ… Built-in | âŒ | âŒ | âœ… |
| **Protocol Support** | **HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2** with intelligent fallback | HTTP/1.1 | HTTP/1.1, HTTP/2 | HTTP/1.1 |
| **Enterprise Features** | âœ… Complete | âš ï¸ Limited | âš ï¸ Limited | âš ï¸ Limited |
| **Memory Usage** | ğŸŸ¢ Low | ğŸŸ¡ Medium | ğŸŸ¢ Low | ğŸŸ¡ Medium |

